Install Datree with Helm v3

This will create a new namespace (datree), where Datreeâ€™s services and application resources will reside. datree.token is used to connect this dashboard to your cluster.
helm repo add datree-webhook https://datreeio.github.io/admission-webhook-datree
helm repo update
helm install -n datree datree-webhook datree-webhook/datree-admission-webhook --debug \
--create-namespace \
--set datree.token=********************************c250 \
--set datree.clusterName=$(kubectl config current-context)

